{"lemma":"عُشْبٌ","slug":"عُشْبٌ","root":"ع.ش.ب","root_slug":"ع-ش-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ش-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29177"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fresh, green, juicy, soft or tender herbs or herbage, green grass","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pasture","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew עֵשֶׂב (ʿēśeḇ) and Aramaic עִשְׂבָּא / ܥܷܣܒܳܐ (ʕesbā). Compare also عَشِبَ (ʕašiba, “to dry up, get stale”)."},"ipa":["/ʕuʃb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29177","headword_ar":"عُشْبٌ","root":"E$b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a coll. gen. n.], n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh, green, juicy, soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the first part of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEu AlkalaA^a","text_ar":"رَبِيعُ الكَلَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which begins in January and ends in March, O. S.]: (Msb:) not termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$iy$N","text_ar":"حَشِيشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"until drying up: (S, O:) or, in the opinion of the generality of the lexicologists,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obN","text_ar":"عُشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is fresh"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$iy$N","text_ar":"حَشِيشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earliest, of herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraEaAnu AlkalaA^i","text_ar":"سَرَعَانُ الكَلَاِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afterwards"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dries up, and does not remain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaA^N","text_ar":"كَلَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being applied by the Arabs to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$ob","text_ar":"عُشْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to other kinds: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obN","text_ar":"عُشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh, green, juicy, soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants, of the desert, that come forth in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":": and under this term are included"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those that are hard and thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which are termed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwr","text_ar":"ذُكُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; as well as to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those that are slender and soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which are termed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAr","text_ar":"اَحْرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: or, accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever is destroyed by winter, and grows again from the stocks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roots, thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"he says also that it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as is uninterrupted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaA$iybu","text_ar":"تَعَاشِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to Th, it is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as so opposed. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obapu Ald~aAri","text_ar":"عُشْبَةُ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The green herb of the dwelling"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which grows in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimonap","text_ar":"دِمْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"patch of ground which people have blackened by their cooking and where their cattle have staled and dunged"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the dwelling, surrounded by fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green, herbs, in a white"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clean"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the ground, and good soil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajiynap","text_ar":"هَجِينَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woman whose father is a free man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an Arab, and her mother a slave"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; an appellation like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u AlwaDari","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ الوَضَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. lit. meaning “ The green herb that grows in the place where the water with which skins have been washed, or the like, is poured out: ” but IbrD thinks that it may be a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u Ald~imani","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ الدِّمَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obu Al*~iy^obi","text_ar":"عُشْبُ الذِّيْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eyptian toad-flax; antirrhinum Aegyptiacum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the name of which is written by Forskål (Flora Aegypt. Arab., pp. lxviii. and 112,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$b Aldyb","text_ar":"عشب الديب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Asjib ed dîb"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aeschib ed dîb."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}